HEADWORD: Epipolized
<hw>E*pip"o*lized</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Changed to the
epipolic condition, or that in which the phenomenon of fluorescence is
presented; produced by fluorescence; <as>as, <ex>epipolized</ex>
light</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Stokes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

